  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Making deep learning go brrrr from first principles (2022)",
      "url": "https://horace.io/brrr_intro.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48246889",
      "score": 175,
      "comments": 63,
      "author": "tosh",
      "published": "2026-05-23T11:50:22Z",
      "bullets": [
        "GPU performance is constrained by memory bandwidth (HBM vs. SRAM) rather than raw compute FLOPs for many modern deep learning operations.",
        "Eager mode PyTorch introduces high kernel launch overheads; compiling graphs enables kernel fusion to reduce memory roundtrips to HBM.",
        "Compilers like PyTorch 2.0 (torch.compile) and Triton automate kernel fusion, optimizing memory-bound bottlenecks like LayerNorm and Softmax."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "libwce: the entropy layer of a wavelet codec, on its own",
      "url": "https://yogthos.net/posts/2026-05-24-libwce.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/d3uwf1",
      "score": 1,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "Yogthos",
      "published": "2026-05-24T13:43:11Z",
      "bullets": [
        "libwce isolates a wavelet codec's entropy coding layer, separating statistical compression from the initial mathematical wavelet transform.",
        "This decoupling allows engineers to apply optimized context-based arithmetic coding to custom multi-resolution data structures and non-image signals.",
        "Standardizing this layer enables independent optimization of bit-plane coding pipelines without rewriting core compression and serialization logic."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Debian SE Linux and PinTheft",
      "url": "https://etbe.coker.com.au/2026/05/24/debian-selinux-pintheft/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/jlhsqw",
      "score": 3,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "7tehdt3cnw6kir6o",
      "published": "2026-05-24T11:37:11Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Debian's default SELinux policies may fail to properly isolate `pinentry` processes, exposing them to local inter-process attacks.",
        "Attackers can exploit insufficient ptrace restrictions to scrape active GnuPG passphrases and smart card PINs directly from memory.",
        "Mitigate this vector by enabling Yama ptrace scope limitations (`kernel.yama.ptrace_scope=1`) and hardening SELinux policy domains."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "Kubernetes In Anger",
      "url": "https://samof76.space/kubernetes-in-anger.html",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/iggblv",
      "score": 26,
      "comments": 12,
      "author": "samof76",
      "published": "2026-05-21T10:27:31Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Production Kubernetes requires careful etcd tuning, high-performance storage, and defragmentation to avoid quorum loss and control plane latency under load.",
        "CoreDNS scaling issues and ndots:5 latency overhead frequently plague large-scale deployments; mitigate using NodeLocal DNSCache and custom IPAM configurations.",
        "Incorrect CPU limits trigger CFS throttling, while misconfigured memory requests lead to unexpected OOMKilled events; use VPA for dynamic rightsizing."
      ]
    },
